verbose_text: The follow-up work carried out by Zhao et al found that a series of podocarpic acid derivatives (compound 2, Figure XREF_FIG) exhibited potent activities (EC 50 = 140-640 nM) against a cell-line adapted influenza virus (A/Puerto Rico/8/34, PR8, an oseltamivir and amantadine resist H1N1 strain) infection of MDCK (Madin-Darby canine kidney) cells XREF_BIBR.
